<h2 id=3D"DataStructuresandAlgorithms-=F0=9F=A7=A91.Heaps">=F0=9F=A7=A9 <st=
rong>1. Heaps</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> A <strong>complete binary tree</strong> tha=
t satisfies the <strong>heap property</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Heap Property:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Max-Heap:</strong> Parent =E2=89=A5 Children</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Min-Heap:</strong> Parent =E2=89=A4 Children</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"DataStructuresandAlgorithms-Operations"><strong>Operations</stron=
g></h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Insert:</strong> Add element and heapify =E2=86=92 O(log n)</p><=
/li>
<li>
<p><strong>Delete (usually root):</strong> Remove root, replace with last e=
lement, heapify =E2=86=92 O(log n)</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Peek:</strong> Access root =E2=86=92 O(1)</p></li>
</ol>
<h3 id=3D"DataStructuresandAlgorithms-Applications"><strong>Applications</s=
trong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Priority queues</p></li>
<li>
<p>Heap sort</p></li>
<li>
<p>Scheduling algorithms</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"DataStructuresandAlgorithms-=F0=9F=A7=A92.FibonacciHeaps">=F0=9F=
=A7=A9 <strong>2. Fibonacci Heaps</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> A <strong>heap-based data structure</strong=
> optimized for <strong>decrease-key and merge operations</strong>.</p></li=
>
<li>
<p><strong>Structure:</strong> Collection of <strong>heap-ordered trees</st=
rong> with <strong>lazy consolidation</strong></p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Operations:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Insert: O(1) amortized</p></li>
<li>
<p>Find-min: O(1)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Extract-min: O(log n) amortized</p></li>
<li>
<p>Decrease-key: O(1) amortized</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"DataStructuresandAlgorithms-Applications.1"><strong>Applications<=
/strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Graph algorithms: <strong>Dijkstra=E2=80=99s shortest path</strong>, <st=
rong>Prim=E2=80=99s MST</strong></p></li>
<li>
<p>Priority queue with <strong>frequent key decreases</strong></p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"DataStructuresandAlgorithms-=F0=9F=A7=A93.B-Trees">=F0=9F=A7=A9 <=
strong>3. B-Trees</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> A <strong>balanced search tree</strong> opt=
imized for <strong>disk storage</strong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Properties:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>All leaves at the same level</p></li>
<li>
<p>Each node can have <strong>multiple keys and children</strong></p></li>
<li>
<p>Maintains <strong>sorted order</strong> for fast search, insert, delete<=
/p></li>
</ol></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"DataStructuresandAlgorithms-Operations.1"><strong>Operations</str=
ong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Search: O(log n)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Insert: O(log n)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Delete: O(log n)</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"DataStructuresandAlgorithms-Applications.2"><strong>Applications<=
/strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Databases and file systems</p></li>
<li>
<p>Indexing large datasets</p></li>
<li>
<p>Multi-level storage systems</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"DataStructuresandAlgorithms-=F0=9F=A7=A94.B+Trees">=F0=9F=A7=A9 <=
strong>4. B+ Trees</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> Variant of B-Tree with <strong>all values s=
tored in leaf nodes</strong> and <strong>internal nodes store only keys</st=
rong>.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Features:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>Leaf nodes linked =E2=86=92 fast <strong>range queries</strong></p></li>
<li>
<p>Internal nodes only guide search =E2=86=92 efficient <strong>disk access=
</strong></p></li>
</ol></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"DataStructuresandAlgorithms-Applications.3"><strong>Applications<=
/strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Database indexing</p></li>
<li>
<p>File systems (e.g., NTFS, Oracle, MySQL)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Efficient range queries and sequential access</p></li>
</ul>
