<p>Parallel algorithms;</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Perfect =F0=9F=91=8F =E2=80=94 now let=E2=80=99s cover <strong>Parallel =
Algorithms</strong>, an important topic in <strong>advanced algorithm desig=
n and computing</strong>. I=E2=80=99ll explain step by step.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"DataStructuresandAlgorithms-=F0=9F=A7=A91.WhatareParallelAlgorith=
ms?">=F0=9F=A7=A9 <strong>1. What are Parallel Algorithms?</strong></h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Definition:</strong> Algorithms designed to <strong>divide a pro=
blem into subproblems</strong> that can be solved <strong>simultaneously</s=
trong> using multiple processors.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Goal:</strong> Reduce <strong>execution time</strong> by perform=
ing multiple computations at once.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Used in <strong>high-performance computing, multi-core processors, and d=
istributed systems</strong>.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"DataStructuresandAlgorithms-=F0=9F=A7=A92.KeyConcepts.1">=F0=9F=
=A7=A9 <strong>2. Key Concepts</strong></h2>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Parallelism:</strong> Performing multiple operations <strong>at =
the same time</strong></p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Speedup (S):</strong><br>
[<br>
S =3D \frac{\text{Time taken by sequential algorithm}}{\text{Time taken by =
parallel algorithm}}<br>
]</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Efficiency (E):</strong><br>
[<br>
E =3D \frac{\text{Speedup}}{\text{Number of processors}}<br>
]</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Granularity:</strong> Size of subproblems;</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Fine-grained:</strong> Many small tasks</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Coarse-grained:</strong> Few large tasks</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"DataStructuresandAlgorithms-=F0=9F=A7=A93.TypesofParallelism">=F0=
=9F=A7=A9 <strong>3. Types of Parallelism</strong></h2>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Data Parallelism:</strong> Same operation on <strong>different p=
ieces of data</strong> simultaneously</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Example: Vector addition, matrix multiplication</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Task Parallelism:</strong> Different tasks executed <strong>in p=
arallel</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Example: Pipeline processing, independent function execution</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ol>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"DataStructuresandAlgorithms-=F0=9F=A7=A94.CommonParallelAlgorithm=
s">=F0=9F=A7=A9 <strong>4. Common Parallel Algorithms</strong></h2>
