</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<p>=E2=9C=85 <strong>In Short:</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>NP-Complete problems</strong> are the hardest problems in NP; so=
lutions can be verified quickly but not necessarily found quickly.<br><stro=
ng>NP-Hard problems</strong> may be even harder and are not guaranteed to b=
e verifiable in polynomial time.<br>
Understanding these classes is crucial for <strong>algorithm design and com=
putational feasibility</strong>.</p>
</blockquote>
